{
  "texts": [
    "It fosters continuous improvement and learning within the team.2) Artifacts: a) Product backlog: A prioritized list of a product's desired features, enhancements, and fixes.",
    "It serves as the single source of requirements for the team and is continuously refined and reprioritized.b) Sprint backlog: A subset of the product backlog containing the user stories and tasks the team commits to completing during a sprint.",
    "It helps the team focus on the work in the current sprint.c) Increment: The sum of all the completed and potentially shippable product backlog items at the end of a sprint.",
    "It represents the tangible outcome of a sprint and provides value to stakeholders.",
    "d) Burn-down chart: A visual representation of the remaining work (usually measured in story points or tasks) throughout a sprint."
  ]
}